			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">gcc normally assumes that the stack is 16-byte-aligned, and part of the reason for this assumption is to allow fast SSE 16-byte load/stores to the stack, which require alignment.

I added a test, tests/stack_alignment/sse_alignment_test.c, for this.

However, I haven't seen this fail because gcc 4.4 is not making use of its assumption for SSE stack accesses.

So, when we switch to gcc 4.5 we should check that it generates &amp;quot;movaps&amp;quot; instead of &amp;quot;movlps&amp;quot;/&amp;quot;movhps&amp;quot; for stack accesses.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-02-16T09:05:28.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-10-21T13:00:18.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
